# ── SET THESE IN RAILWAY DASHBOARD → Variables tab ──────────

# Any random string (used to secure sessions)
SECRET_KEY=make-this-something-random-like-sumwon2026dashboard

# Password for the /upload page — only you and your team know this
UPLOAD_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-password

# ── DEPLOY STEPS ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. CREATE A GITHUB REPO
#    - Go to github.com → New repository → Private
#    - Name it: sumwon-dashboard
#    - Upload all files from this folder into it
#
# 2. DEPLOY ON RAILWAY
#    - Go to railway.app → New Project
#    - Click "Deploy from GitHub repo"
#    - Select sumwon-dashboard
#    - Railway builds automatically (takes ~2 min)
#    - You get a live URL like: sumwon-dashboard.up.railway.app
#
# 3. SET ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
#    - Railway dashboard → your service → Variables tab
#    - Add: SECRET_KEY and UPLOAD_PASSWORD from above
#    - Click Deploy to restart with new vars
#
# 4. DONE — YOUR DASHBOARD IS LIVE
#    - Upload page: your-url.railway.app/upload
#    - Dashboard:   your-url.railway.app/dashboard
#
# ── WEEKLY WORKFLOW (every Monday, 2 minutes) ────────────────
#
# 1. Export 4 CSVs from BigQuery (same queries as always)
# 2. Go to your-url.railway.app/upload
# 3. Enter password → drop 4 files → click Upload
# 4. Dashboard refreshes instantly with all data
# 5. Share your-url.railway.app with CEO
#
# Each BigQuery export includes full history (W15 onwards),
# so every upload automatically contains all previous weeks.
# The CEO can navigate any week from the dropdown.
#
# ── FILE SLOTS ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Slot 1 (SHEIN Revenue)    → Weekly_Trade_Table_2.csv
# Slot 2 (Inventory)        → Weekly_Trade_Table_1.csv
# Slot 3 (Hit Rate Cohort)  → Weekly_Trade_2-31_Cohort.csv
# Slot 4 (Webshop Data)     → Webshop_per_Site_per_Week.csv
#
# File names don't need to match exactly — just pick the
# right slot for each file when uploading.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
